<p>LADWP operates under California's net metering rules, allowing solar customers to receive full retail rate credits for excess electricity sent back to the grid. This means when your Los Angeles solar system produces more electricity than your home consumes, you receive credits at the full 24.2¬¢/kWh rate. These credits roll over month-to-month and are reconciled annually, providing maximum value for solar production. LADWP requires an interconnection agreement for all solar installations, and the utility typically completes the approval process within 2-4 weeks after receiving proper documentation from your installer.</p>

